  if (ICmpInst::isEquality(Cond))
    return true;
  assert(ICmpInst::isUnsigned(Cond));
  return NW != GEPNoWrapFlags::none();
};
```

This is too permissive. The `nuw` flag alone doesn't guarantee that unsigned comparison of pointers equals unsigned comparison of offsets when offsets can be negative. The fix should require `nusw` (or `inbounds` which implies `nusw`) for unsigned comparisons, not just any nowrap flag.

